    "author_channel_id": "UCX0fW4n0zee_KxaLGrAYWtw",
    "text": "Hi very good. I worked as a production engineer in 1981. I had to tool up for a TV tube making machine for India. No matter how accurately you tried to machine the cam and follower, on first fit it would shake, which was fatal to the tubes. Only an adjustable fixture, with you which progressively equalized the distance between and orientation of the six slots until  all perfect, would give a perfect smooth motion. Great days! Love your projects.",
